Living near congested roads with high levels of air pollution can cause ` silent strokes ' which increase the risk of dementia , scientists say .
Exposure to small , sooty particles , mostly caused by traffic fumes and factory emissions , alters the structure of the brain .
The microscopic particles have been shown to cause lung damage in blood vessels and clotting , thought to contribute to the deaths of 29,000 people every year in Britain .
